    "shortDesc": "Encounter for screening for malignant neoplasm of colon",
    "longDesc": "Encounter for screening for malignant neoplasm of colon",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a doctor's visit where the main purpose is to screen you for colon cancer, even though you don't have any symptoms or known problems. During screening, a doctor typically performs a colonoscopy (a procedure where a camera on a tube is inserted into your colon to look for polyps or early signs of cancer) or other tests like stool samples or imaging to catch cancer early before it causes any harm.",
    "whoUses": "Gastroenterologists, primary care physicians, and colorectal surgeons use this code during routine preventive care visits and cancer screening procedures. This code commonly appears on EOB statements because it's covered by most insurance plans as part of preventive health services, typically for adults age 45 and older (or 50+, depending on guidelines).",
