    "code": "Z12.31",
    "rawCode": "Z1231",
    "shortDesc": "Encntr screen mammogram for malignant neoplasm of breast",
    "longDesc": "Encounter for screening mammogram for malignant neoplasm of breast",
    "plainEnglish": "This code represents a visit to get a mammogram—an X-ray image of the breast—specifically to check for breast cancer when you don't have any symptoms. Mammograms are routine screening tests that can detect cancer early, before you might feel a lump or notice other signs. This is a preventive health visit, not a diagnostic one, meaning you're getting checked as part of regular cancer prevention rather than because of a suspected problem.",
    "whoUses": "Obstetrician-gynecologists, primary care physicians, radiologists, and family medicine doctors use this code when ordering routine breast cancer screening. This code frequently appears on insurance EOB statements as a preventive care visit and is often covered without cost-sharing under most insurance plans due to preventive health care benefits.",
