    "code": "Z13.88",
    "rawCode": "Z1388",
    "shortDesc": "Encntr screen for disorder due to exposure to contaminants",
    "longDesc": "Encounter for screening for disorder due to exposure to contaminants",
    "plainEnglish": "This code is used when you visit a doctor for a checkup to see if you've been exposed to harmful substances like chemicals, radiation, asbestos, or pollution that could make you sick. The visit itself isn't because you're already ill, but rather as a precaution to catch any health problems early before they cause serious damage. Think of it like a screening test after a potential toxic exposure, similar to getting checked after a workplace accident or environmental incident.",
    "whoUses": "Occupational health physicians, environmental medicine specialists, and primary care doctors use this code when patients come in for preventive screening after known or suspected exposure to hazardous materials. It commonly appears in workplace health programs, post-disaster medical evaluations, and environmental health clinics, though it's less frequently seen on routine patient EOB statements compared to other screening codes.",
