    "longDesc": "Encounter for supervision of normal first pregnancy, unspecified trimester",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a routine check-up visit during a woman's first pregnancy when everything is developing normally and there are no complications. The visit is for monitoring and supervision of the pregnancy to ensure both mother and baby are healthy, but no specific trimester (first three months, second three months, or third three months) was documented. These are standard prenatal care appointments that happen throughout pregnancy to check vital signs, baby's growth, and address any questions or concerns.",
