    "longDesc": "Other long term (current) drug therapy",
    "plainEnglish": "This code indicates that a patient is currently taking a long-term medication that doesn't fit into the other standard categories (like insulin, blood thinners, or antibiotics). It's used when someone needs to document ongoing use of a medication—often for chronic conditions—but that medication doesn't have its own specific tracking code. For example, this might apply to someone taking a specialty drug for a rare condition or an unusual maintenance medication that requires documentation for insurance or medical records.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by primary care physicians, specialists, and hospital coders when documenting a patient's current medications during office visits, hospital stays, or routine check-ups. It commonly appears on EOB statements when insurance companies need to track ongoing medication use for billing, prior authorization, or medical necessity purposes.",
